Software Engineering Report on Employee Management System (Spring Boot)

Introduction
This report documents the application of modern software engineering principles to the design and implementation of the Employee Management System backend, developed during industrial training at Uneecops Technologies Ltd. The system is implemented with Java Spring Boot and MySQL, focusing on secure and scalable management of employee data. The full project is available on GitHub: https://github.com/ShashankGoutam/EmployeeManagement_SpringBoot

Motivation and Objectives
- Bridge the gap between classroom theory and enterprise backend development practices.
- Design and implement RESTful APIs for employee management.
- Ensure robust authentication and data security using OAuth2 social logins and JWT tokens.
- Maintain high code quality, test coverage, and clear documentation.

