Software Engineering Principles Applied
- Requirements Engineering: All entities and workflows were defined before implementation to ensure system robustness.
- Modular Design: The system is architected around modular RESTful controllers and service layers, supporting extension and maintenance.
- Database Design: Normalized employee schema and ER diagrams ensure data consistency and efficient access.
- Security: OAuth2, JWT, and bearer token-based authentication restrict system access to authorized users.
- Documentation & Testing: Comprehensive API documentation via Swagger, system-level testing with Postman, and unit/integration coverage using JUnit and Mockito.

